com.interpss.core.aclf
Interface AclfBranch

All Superinterfaces:
Branch, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ExtensionElement, IAclfBranch, IAclfBranchAdaptation, IAclfBranchAdjustment, IAclfBranchFunc, IAdaptable, IBranchSwitchBreakModel, NameTag, NetworkedElement, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
All Known Subinterfaces:
AcscBranch
All Known Implementing Classes:
AclfBranchImpl, AcscBranchImpl
public interface AclfBranch
extends Branch, IAclfBranch, IAclfBranchFunc, IAclfBranchAdaptation, IAclfBranchAdjustment

A representation of the model object 'Branch'. AclfBranch class is for storing branch information for AC loadflow analysis. AclfBranch could be extended using IAclfbranch interface.

The following features are supported:

  • Branch Code
  • Z
  • HShunt Y
  • From Turn Ratio
  • To Turn Ratio
  • From Shunt Y
  • To Shunt Y
  • From PS Xfr Angle
  • To PS Xfr Angle
  • Rating Mva1
  • Rating Mva2
  • Rating Mva3
  • Rating Amps
  • Loss Factor
  • Dclf Flow
  • Flow Control

See Also:
AclfPackage.getAclfBranch()

current

double current(Unit.UnitType unit)
Calculate branch current in the unit specified. For Xfr or PSXfr branch, current is calculated at the high voltage side. The current does not include the effect of to from-side shunt Y and the to-side shunt Y.
